description:
Had my first cup of Philz and it was bliss. 

// LOCATION // In the TL on Van Ness. This location is sprawling. On one side of the door is the actual coffee shop and on the other side is a great sit-down area with cushy seats and tables for gossiping or doing work. 

// PARKING // Metered parking if you can snag it. We went on a Saturday morning and were lucky that there were plenty of spots Eddy. $0.25/10 min?  

// SERVICE // Top notch. The barista was so helpful in explaining the different teas and strengths of coffee. Polite, knowledgable, and friendly. The method to get your drinks there is a bit unconventional but I was lucky that I went with some Philz Coffee veterans: 
     +Order coffee straight from the barista. They will ask you if you want cream and sugar as well
     +(optional) step to bagel counter and order a delish bagel with all the toppings
     +Step to the cashier counter, tell the cashier what you ordered, and pay for your drinks/food
     +When your drinks/food is ready, they will call out your order.
     +Sip the delish brew and enjoy!
